    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI noticed that as of PR #25395, the cursor can disappear during movements in certain scenarios. Here's a minimal reproducible example.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if the behavior is expected/intended in certain scenarios, so I thought I'd report it here.\r\n\r\nCc: @bfredl \r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n```\r\n\r\nCreate `example.lua`, with the following text. Be sure to insert many (e.g., 100) blank lines at the end of the file, to have more room for cursor movement in the steps that follow.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('CursorMoved', {\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    vim.defer_fn(function()\r\n      for i = 0, 20 do\r\n\tvim.o.textwidth = 80\r\n      end\r\n    end, 0)\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('OptionSet', {\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    vim.cmd('redrawstatus!')\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n\r\n-- <INSERT MANY BLANK LINES>\r\n```\r\n\r\nSource the file:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:source %\r\n```\r\n\r\nVertically split the window:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:vsplit\r\n```\r\n\r\nGo to the top of the file:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\ngg\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen hold `j` to move the cursor, which will disappear:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\njjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjj\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the cursor to show during movement, as was the case prior to PR #25395.\r\n\r\nThe following video shows cursor movement before and after sourcing the script. Before, the cursor shows during movement. After, the cursor disappears.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/541289/e30e8aac-3f3d-42dc-9000-360e8d48e7f6\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1242+ge33269578\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nKubuntu 23.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKonsole 22.12.3\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
